news.title: JSW Steel acquires 30.5-acre land parcel in Pen near Mumbai
news.para: The company has purchased the land parcel for Rs 23.22 crore and had paid nearly Rs 14.82 crore as advance payment towards the same in December 2018.

news.title: Property holders in Punjab to get NOC in 15 days: Minister
news.para: At a meeting held here at Punjab Bhawan, Cheema proposed that NoC be issued in 5 working days under Tatkal for the convenience of NRIs and other such persons who need it in a short time span.

news.title: Century Real Estate in talks with global & domestic funds to raise over Rs 1000 crore
news.para: The company, which currently has a 2.5 million sq ft portfolio of commercial properties, plans to double its office portfolio in the next four to five years.

news.title: New home sales fall in U.S. in September; prices remain high
news.para: New home sales decreased 10.9% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 603,000 units last month, the Commerce Department said on Wednesday. August's sales pace was revised down to 677,000 units from the previously reported 685,000 units.

news.title: Hong Kong home prices drop 2.1% in September 2022
news.para: The property price index was at 362.1 in September, down 9% from an all-time peak of 398.1 in September last year. Home prices in the financial hub have fallen 8.1% in the first nine months of this year.

news.title: Bhubaneswar civic body to create model slum in each ward
news.para: In May, the slum tag had been removed from 135 localities. Now, out of those slums, the officials have selected 10 to develop into model slums.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: 1.10 lakh Tidco houses to be given by December 2022
news.para: The chief minister held a review meeting with the officials of the housing department at his Tadepalli camp office. He cautioned the officials that the Tidco houses should not become slums in future due to bad maintenance.

news.title: Bihar CM inaugurates 65 three-storey houses for MLAs in Patna
news.para: While inspecting the newly built houses, the CM asked the BCD officials to maintain cleanliness in the premises and expedite the construction of the rest 178 three-storey houses for the MLAs and 20 duplex houses for the MLCs.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body all set to link its rental properties with UID number
news.para: Besides, the MC is planning to give different colour coding to MC rental properties and the officials claimed they had to recover Rs 11.49 crore in dues from its tenants.

news.title: Goa: Process for issuing health NOCs for new buildings eased
news.para: The public health department has stated that mere ‘technical clearance/development plan’ issued by the town and country planning department (TCP) is sufficient for issuing health NOCs for construction of any building, house, and other structure.

news.title: Officials seek over Rs 2,000 crore for housing scheme in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The Government of India has already released Rs 4,032 crore under PMAY-U so far in the 2022-23 financial year but the AP government released only Rs 2,556 crore of the grant to the Housing Department, diverting another Rs 1,476 crore.

news.title: Despite district court order, builder 'denies' power supply to 550 Pivotal Devaan families
news.para: Residents claimed that they have been without electricity since Tuesday as the developer has disconnected supply for their refusal to to pay between Rs 52,000 and Rs 82,000 as extra electrification development charges.

news.title: Indian Railways to club realty monetisation with revamp of stations
news.para: Railways had removed associated real estate monetisation as part of station redevelopment but is now reverting to the original plan following concerns about the private sector being unable to recover investment from station usage fee.

news.title: Rs 32.4 lakh fine imposed over non-compliance of dust norms in Delhi
news.para: User agencies of construction and demolition projects larger than 500 square metres are required to register them on the construction and demolition (C&D) portal launched in October last year in a bid to control dust pollution in the capital.

news.title: Skanska says rising interest rates, costs dim outlook in Europe
news.para: Third-quarter order bookings in Skanska's construction arm rose by 50% from a year earlier and by 17.4% versus the second quarter to 43.8 billion Swedish crowns adjusted for currency effects.
